# Buildroot defconfig — ADOS lite agent on Luckfox Pico Zero (RV1106G3).
#
# This file is a DELTA on top of the stock Luckfox Pico Zero defconfig that
# the upstream Luckfox SDK ships at:
#   <luckfox-sdk>/sysdrv/source/buildroot/buildroot-2024.02/configs/
# The full settings tree (toolchain triplet, kernel headers, init system,
# rootfs format) lives in the SDK and we do not duplicate those here — pulling
# them in by mistake would force this file to track upstream toolchain churn.
#
# How to use:
#   1. Copy the upstream stock defconfig to this path with the ADOS suffix:
#        cp <upstream> luckfox_pico_zero_ados_defconfig
#   2. Apply the deltas listed below (uncomment lines, add packages).
#   3. Drop into <buildroot>/configs/ via BR2_EXTERNAL_ADOS_PATH. Build with:
#        make luckfox_pico_zero_ados_defconfig
#        make
#
# The deltas below are additive — we do not flip any upstream selection off,
# we only add the packages the lite agent needs. Stock Luckfox already gives
# us busybox sysv-rc init, uclibc rootfs, and the Rockchip kernel, which is
# exactly what the lite-agent musl-static binary is built against.

#
# === ADOS lite agent + its prerequisites ===
#

# Lite agent binary + init scripts + default agent.yaml. See
# package/ados-agent-lite/ for the recipe body.
BR2_PACKAGE_ADOS_AGENT_LITE=y

#
# === Networking ===
#

# Wi-Fi userspace. The AIC8800DC out-of-tree driver is provided as a separate
# package once the kernel-side bits land in the upstream Buildroot tree.
BR2_PACKAGE_WPA_SUPPLICANT=y

# DHCP client. busybox udhcpc is in by default; uncomment dhcpcd if the
# operator profile prefers it (slightly more compliant on multi-iface boards).
# BR2_PACKAGE_DHCPCD=y

# NTP — agent timestamps need real time. chrony is the lighter daemon and
# comes up under busybox sysv-rc cleanly.
BR2_PACKAGE_CHRONY=y

# SSH for bench / debug. Dropbear (~200 KB) over OpenSSH (~2 MB) on the lite
# rootfs. Configure root login disabled by default at first boot via the
# overlay; operators add an authorized_keys via the setup webapp later.
BR2_PACKAGE_DROPBEAR=y

#
# === Wi-Fi adapter for WFB-ng (air-side) ===
#

# RTL8812AU/EU out-of-tree driver, used for WFB-ng broadcast on the air side.
# The Buildroot package name varies across SDK forks. The Luckfox SDK does
# not ship this package today; it must be added as a Buildroot patch alongside
# the WFB-ng orchestration work. Until then this line is a TODO marker; the
# kernel module is loaded out-of-tree at install time on a regular Buildroot
# image, and bench operators can sideload via the same path.
# BR2_PACKAGE_RTL8812AU=y

#
# === Hardware enablement ===
#

# udev for device-node management. busybox mdev is the stock alternative on
# minimal Buildroot but doesn't gracefully handle USB hotplug for the
# AIC8800DC SDIO bring-up sequence; eudev is the right call here.
BR2_PACKAGE_EUDEV=y

# Linux kernel headers — already pulled by the agent toolchain, but we set
# this explicitly so kernel module DKMS rebuilds work on-image when an
# operator sideloads a Wi-Fi driver.
# BR2_TOOLCHAIN_HEADERS_AT_LEAST_5_10=y  # set in upstream stock defconfig

#
# === Tools the operator can rely on at first-boot ===
#

# wget is in busybox by default. The lite installer prefers curl; including
# both costs ~80 KB and removes a fork-error path on the first install
# attempt over the setup webapp.
BR2_PACKAGE_LIBCURL=y
BR2_PACKAGE_LIBCURL_CURL=y

# minisign for OTA verification (matches scripts/install-lite.sh contract).
# If the upstream Buildroot tree doesn't carry a minisign package, vendor it
# under a BR2_EXTERNAL_ADOS_PATH/package/minisign/ recipe instead.
BR2_PACKAGE_MINISIGN=y

# tar (busybox provides) — the lite installer extracts the release tarball
# via `gzip -dc | tar -x -f -` so no extra package is required.

#
# === Filesystem + boot ===
#

# Root filesystem format. The stock Luckfox defconfig already selects the
# right squashfs/ext4 combination for the RV1106 boot chain; we leave that
# alone and only set the rootfs overlay path so /etc/ados/ pre-populates.
BR2_ROOTFS_OVERLAY="$(BR2_EXTERNAL_ADOS_PATH)/board/luckfox_pico_zero/rootfs-overlay"

# Post-image script: gzip + sha256 the resulting .img. The CI workflow
# at .github/workflows/luckfox-image-build.yml also invokes this script
# explicitly after `make` returns, which is harmless when the variable
# below is set (Buildroot runs it once during the build, the workflow
# re-runs it idempotently on the gzipped artifact). Local-build workflows
# that prefer the workflow to do the compression can leave this line
# commented out.
BR2_ROOTFS_POST_IMAGE_SCRIPT="$(BR2_EXTERNAL_ADOS_PATH)/post-image.sh"

#
# === Notes ===
#
# - We deliberately do NOT enable a default-password shell or a debug serial
#   getty without auth gate. The first-boot pairing surface is the only
#   identity-bearing artifact in the image; SSH keys arrive via the setup
#   webapp under operator authentication.
# - We do NOT bake an operator's pair code into the image. Each flashed SBC
#   generates its own at first boot from /etc/machine-id, which is unique per
#   device because Buildroot's first-boot service regenerates it.
